        "title": "fix(scripts): type windows taskkill helper",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add a colocated declaration file for `scripts/lib/windows-taskkill.mjs`.\n- Let TypeScript resolve `resolveWindowsTaskkillPath` from TS scripts such as `scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts`.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nWhile triaging `#93351` after rebasing onto current main, the local `pnpm tsgo:core:test` run reached:\n\n```text\nscripts/control-ui-i18n.ts(11,44): error TS7016: Could not find a declaration file for module './lib/windows-taskkill.mjs'.\n```\n\nThe helper is a JavaScript module used by TypeScript scripts, so current main needs a matching declaration file for the existing export.\n\n## Evidence\nBefore this patch, the current main type check reports TS7016 for the `windows-taskkill.mjs` import in `scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts`.\n\nAfter this patch, a focused TypeScript probe that imports `../scripts/lib/windows-taskkill.mjs` and assigns `resolveWindowsTaskkillPath(...)` to `string` passes with:\n\n```text\npnpm exec tsgo --ignoreConfig --noEmit --target ES2023 --lib ES2023 --module NodeNext --moduleResolution NodeNext --types node --skipLibCheck .artifacts\\windows-taskkill-types-probe.ts\n```\n\n## Tests and validation\n- `pnpm exec tsgo --ignoreConfig --noEmit --target ES2023 --lib ES2023 --module NodeNext --moduleResolution NodeNext --types node --skipLibCheck .artifacts\\windows-taskkill-types-probe.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- Attempted `pnpm tsgo:core:test`; the local full run stalled after progressing past the original TS7016 failure, so I stopped the orphaned `tsgo` process and used the focused probe above for the changed type surface.\n\n## Risk checklist\n- [x] Declaration-only change; no runtime code path changes.\n- [x] No dependency, workflow, or generated artifact changes.\n- [x] Scope is limited to the existing `windows-taskkill.mjs` export.\n\n## Current review state\nReady for maintainer review.",
